<subSubSection id="FEE27BEF9F2E2729FF168071FCC8F980" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B64728649F2E2729FF168071FE9CFA3D" blockId="47.[189,310,1383,1409]" box="[189,310,1383,1409]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading id="ED0F9F089F2E2729FF168071FE9CFA3D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1383,1409]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis id="848CF4769F2E2729FF168071FE9CFA3D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1383,1409]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B64728649F2E2729FF168080FCC8F980" blockId="47.[189,1399,1430,1597]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="71F853E79F2E2729FECE8080FE5CFA13" authority="Kuhlmann, 2014" authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[357,502,1430,1456]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="848CF4769F2E2729FECE8080FE5CFA13" box="[357,502,1430,1456]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9FBF490D9F2E2729FE578080FDFCFA0C" box="[508,598,1430,1456]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from other species of this group by the combination of the following characters: supraclypeal area and clypeus sparsely but distinctly punctate, mostly finely sculptured and slightly matt (
<figureCitation id="2EC334E19F2E2729FDBB80CAFDD3FA4B" box="[528,633,1500,1527]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 25B</figureCitation>
), scutum reticulate, sparsely and shallowly punctate, basal area of propodeum basally indistinctly carinate (
<figureCitation id="2EC334E19F2E2729FD3380E9FD46F9A6" box="[664,748,1535,1562]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
C–D), stigma brown, apical margins of metasomal terga black, terga impunctate (
<figureCitation id="2EC334E19F2E2729FE748334FDE3F981" box="[479,585,1570,1597]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 25E</figureCitation>
). The male is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
